description: Green Wasabi Tobiko Roe is a type of fish roe that is commonly used in sushi and sashimi dishes. Tobiko is the roe of the flying fish and it is known for its bright green color and crunchy texture. Green wasabi Tobiko Roe is made by carefully cleaning, salting and then dying the roe with a natural green coloring. It has a mild, slightly sweet and briny flavor and a crispy texture. It is often used as a garnish on sushi rolls, sashimi and other Japanese dishes. It can also be used as a topping for salads, soups or sandwiches. Green wasabi Tobiko Roe is a flavorful and visually appealing ingredient that adds a unique texture and color to any dish.

description: From the pristine clear waters of the Java Sea come the world's sweetest, most succulent swimming blue crabs. Java Crab's artisan fishermen catch and carefully select only the largest of the species (portunus pelagicus). Following precise sustainability guidelines, they release the egg-bearing females for the enjoyment of future generations. Within hours of harvest, Jave Crab Meat is hand-picked and pasteurized. Ongoing quality control inspections, at our HACCP cerified plant, guarantee the most delicious, virtually shell-free sweet crab meat with a shelf life of 15 months under proper refrigeration. Java Crab Meat is available year-round.

description: Anchovies in oil are small, salted fish that are preserved in oil. They have a rich and savory flavor, and are commonly used as a seasoning or flavoring in a variety of culinary applications. The anchovies are typically packed in oil, which helps to preserve their flavor and texture. They can be used in a wide range of dishes, from classic Caesar salad dressings to pasta sauces, marinades, and even pizzas. Their distinct flavor adds depth and complexity to a wide range of dishes.

description: Anchovies in Oil from Recca are a premium food product made from high-quality anchovy fillets that have been carefully selected and hand-packed in extra-virgin olive oil. These anchovies have a rich, savory flavor and a tender texture that makes them perfect for use in a variety of culinary applications. The anchovies are caught in the Mediterranean Sea, and then immediately processed and packed to ensure maximum freshness and flavor. They are carefully deboned and filleted by hand, and then packed in pure extra-virgin olive oil, which further enhances their flavor. Anchovies in Oil from Recca are a versatile ingredient that can be used to add depth of flavor to a wide range of dishes, including pizzas, pasta sauces, salads, and more.

Our marinated white anchovies are characterized by their meaty texture, which is perfectly complemented by their bold, briny flavor. description: Isola D'Oro anchovy paste is a versatile Italian store cupboard ingredient. Spread a small amount of anchovy paste on pizzas, add to sauces and mix it with Italian cheese and breadcrumbs to make a stuffing for conchiglioni pasta. Isola D'Oro specialises in the curing of fish and seafood, using traditional techniques to bring superb produce to a wide audience. description:
Indulge in the rich, buttery flavor and tender texture of our 6 oz Norwegian Salmon Portions. Sustainably sourced from the cold, clear waters of Norway, these premium salmon portions are carefully hand-cut and trimmed to ensure the highest quality product for your kitchen.

Shelf-stable squid ink is a convenient way to enjoy this delicious ingredient without having to worry about the ink spoiling or going bad. description: Green Wasabi Tobiko Roe is a type of fish roe that is commonly used in sushi and sashimi dishes. Tobiko is the roe of the flying fish and it is known for its bright green color and crunchy texture. Green wasabi Tobiko Roe is made by carefully cleaning, salting and then dying the roe with a natural green coloring. It has a mild, slightly sweet and briny flavor and a crispy texture. It is often used as a garnish on sushi rolls, sashimi and other Japanese dishes. It can also be used as a topping for salads, soups or sandwiches. Green wasabi Tobiko Roe is a flavorful and visually appealing ingredient that adds a unique texture and color to any dish.

description: From the pristine clear waters of the Java Sea come the world's sweetest, most succulent swimming blue crabs. Java Crab's artisan fishermen catch and carefully select only the largest of the species (portunus pelagicus). Following precise sustainability guidelines, they release the egg-bearing females for the enjoyment of future generations. Within hours of harvest, Jave Crab Meat is hand-picked and pasteurized. Ongoing quality control inspections, at our HACCP cerified plant, guarantee the most delicious, virtually shell-free sweet crab meat with a shelf life of 15 months under proper refrigeration. Java Crab Meat is available year-round.

They have a rich and savory flavor, and are commonly used as a seasoning or flavoring in a variety of culinary applications. The anchovies are typically packed in oil, which helps to preserve their flavor and texture. They can be used in a wide range of dishes, from classic Caesar salad dressings to pasta sauces, marinades, and even pizzas. Their distinct flavor adds depth and complexity to a wide range of dishes.

description: Anchovies in Oil from Recca are a premium food product made from high-quality anchovy fillets that have been carefully selected and hand-packed in extra-virgin olive oil. These anchovies have a rich, savory flavor and a tender texture that makes them perfect for use in a variety of culinary applications. The anchovies are caught in the Mediterranean Sea, and then immediately processed and packed to ensure maximum freshness and flavor. They are carefully deboned and filleted by hand, and then packed in pure extra-virgin olive oil, which further enhances their flavor. Anchovies in Oil from Recca are a versatile ingredient that can be used to add depth of flavor to a wide range of dishes, including pizzas, pasta sauces, salads, and more.

description: Isola D'Oro anchovy paste is a versatile Italian store cupboard ingredient. Spread a small amount of anchovy paste on pizzas, add to sauces and mix it with Italian cheese and breadcrumbs to make a stuffing for conchiglioni pasta. Isola D'Oro specialises in the curing of fish and seafood, using traditional techniques to bring superb produce to a wide audience. This Isola D'Oro anchovy paste is mixed with a small amount of olive oil to give it an easily spreadable consistency, perfect for crostini.

description: With its rich, buttery texture and sweet lacing of fruit-wood smoke, it accounts for 80% of our sales. Smoked with the perfect blend of apple and cherry woods, our salmon is praised for its delicate smoked flavor and silky texture. Our salmon comes from the best farms located in the farthest, remotest regions of the icy Northern Atlantic. We receive daily deliveries flown in directly from the farms; more importantly, the salmon we use has never been frozen, giving it an amazingly silky texture, and rich, deep orange color.
name: Fresh Sliced Smoked Salmon

description: Squid ink is a popular ingredient used in many Mediterranean and Italian dishes. It is a dark, black ink extracted from squid and other cephalopods, and it has a distinct salty, briny flavor that is perfect for adding depth and complexity to a variety of recipes. Shelf-stable squid ink is a convenient way to enjoy this delicious ingredient without having to worry about the ink spoiling or going bad. It can be used in a variety of dishes, including pastas, risottos, and seafood stews, as well as in sauces and marinades.
